The defendant Codi B Kissick was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess w/ Intent-THC (>2500-10,000 g) [Modifiers: Conspiracy to Commit], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(h)4.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Codi B. Kissick appeared with attorney Jacob Manian.  Megan Marie Williamson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  sdg

AS TO COUNT 1:

The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of TWO (2) YEARS, consecutive to any other sentence with credit for SIX (6) DAYS time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is ONE (1) YEAR; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is ONE (1) YEAR.  Court took no position as to Electronic Monitoring.

Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program. 

- Court costs, fees, assessments and surcharges, including the DNA surcharge to paid through payment plan at a rate of ONE HUNDRED DOLLARS ($100.00) PER MONTH commencing 05-01-2016 until paid in full.  Any missed payment will result in an entry of civil judgment. 

COURT STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed defendant on probation for EIGHTEEN (18) MONTHS.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/AND CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:

- Court ordered the defendant to serve SEVEN (7) DAYS in the House of Correction.  FORTHWITH.  STRAIGHT TIME.
- Maintain Absolute Sobriety: No use or possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription taken in the manner and fashion as prescribed.
- Department of Corrections must conduct drug and testing.
- No possession of any drug paraphernalia for personal use, manufacturing, delivering or for distribution.
- No possession of any firearms or weapons, firearm ammunition, firearm magazine, firearm holster, or any body armor.
- Obtain and maintain employment or school or vocational training.
- Fine is set at ZERO.
- Drivers license suspension not imposed.
- Provide DNA sample, if not already done.
- NO CONTACT WITH SUSAN S., CYNTHIA M., RUSSELL D.

Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.

The Court informed the defendant of requirements and penalties applicable under s. 941.29(1m) or (4m).
Court advises the Defendant that under Wisconsin Statute 302.113 the amount actually served may be extended, and that the Defendant could serve the entire bifurcated sentence in prison. The Defendant will be subject to certain conditions while on release to extended supervision, and a violation of any of those conditions may result in the Defendant being returned to prison.

AS TO AMENDED COUNT 1 :

The defendant was advised of her Constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Jury Instructions and Addendum to Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.

Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting. Defendant further advised that if she is not a US citizen deportation is possible. 

Parties advised the Court will listen to statements by counsel, any victims, and the defendant. Any other statements must be in writing and provided to the Court 3 business days in advance of the sentencing.
